column2: Fluvial flood hazard maps for Central Asia, derived from a regional model. Filenaming: FLU_DEF_XXy_ZZZ.tif (XX= return period, ZZZ= country initials). Cell value gives maximum flood depth (m) expected for the return period of that raster dataset. Due to file size, this is a partial set of data covering 1-in-5-50y return period. See dataset “Central Asia fluvial flood hazard maps - defended – KAZ 100-1000y RP” for the remaining data.
